## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of economy in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Economy is the bounded circulation structure
through which value generation,
exchange,
allocation,
storage,
and consequence
become meaningful across actors and institutions.

Economy is not a single ledger line
and not identical to finance.
Economy is the broader value-flow environment
within which finance becomes one formalized substructure.

## architectural_position
Economy sits between:
- market and trade exchange
- work and company output
- finance and settlement consequence
- nation policy influence
- asset and inventory value movement

## required_behavior
- economic context must remain explicit
- value-flow basis must remain explicit
- current and historical economic states must remain distinguishable
- local and cross-domain value effects must remain reviewable

## canonical_rules
- projected value must not overwrite source truth
- exchange visibility must not imply ownership truth
- historical economic trace must remain queryable
- ambiguous economic scope fails closed

## state_model
The economy domain distinguishes:
- declared economic context
- active economic flow
- restricted economic flow
- transformed economic state
- historical economic state

## actor_boundary
- participant
- operator
- reviewer
- regulator
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if economic context is unclear, stop economy-sensitive action
- if value-flow basis is unclear, fail closed
- if cross-domain impact is unclear, route to review
- if state becomes historical, preserve trace

## review_checklist
- economic context is explicit
- value-flow basis is explicit
- cross-domain effect is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
